a-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533709\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 26, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xgd1665702875492.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xgd1665702875492.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xgd1665702875492.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xgd1665702875492\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Wide Character Packing Code (W)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The W (wide character) packing code is used for Unicode characters.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xgd1665702875492__p_d44828e1_d44829e1_d44830e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">W</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var> can contain\n            <var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var> characters regardless how many bytes are needed for the\n         characters.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xgd1665702875492__p_d44831e1_d44832e1_d44833e1\">Some databases support only Unicode BMP (Basic Multilingual Plane ), or do not support Unicode at all. To control the behavior of the <code class=\"ph codeph\">W</code> packing code in such circumstances, you can use the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Wide Character Behavior</span> property of the entity interface or the assignment setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$WIDE_CHAR_BEHAVIOR</span>.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"xgd1665702875492__note_w4437ab1b5b5_w4438ab1b5_w4439ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Setting the assignment setting or\n      property to use the character set, switches the W packing code to a C packing code, in which\n      case you must also set the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DEF_CHARSET</span> assignment setting or\n        <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Character Set</span> entity interface property.</div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uir1665702875362.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Packing Codes for Unicode</a><p>By default, the W packing code is for Unicode characters. The U* packing code can also be used for holding Unicode characters. If the entity character set is Unicode, the C packing code can also be used for Unicode characters.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tzj1665702875634.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Character Packing Code (C)</a><p>The C packing code is used for String data types.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rxi1665702670406.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Packing Codes for Other Data</a><p>String, Image, and Raw data can be mapped to a variety of packing codes, including W for Unicode characters.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/blo1665702710364.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Wide Character Behavior</a><p>Specify the character set used for String fields with the W packing code. If the database does not support Unicode, or it supports only Unicode BMP, use this setting to change its behavior. Valid values are Unicode, BMP, or Use Character Set.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wzv1665702719081.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$WIDE_CHAR_BEHAVIOR</a><p>Specify the character set used for String fields with the W packing code.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/azs1665703222737.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$DEF_CHARSET</a><p>Specify the default character set used for storing data in String fields with C packing code.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533709\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533709\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Wide Character Packing Code (W) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 26, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Wide Character Packing Code (W) The W (wide character) packing code is used for Unicode characters. W n can contain n characters regardless how many bytes are needed for the characters. Some databases support only Unicode BMP (Basic Multilingual Plane ), or do not support Unicode at all. To control the behavior of the W packing code in such circumstances, you can use the Wide Character Behavior property of the entity interface or the assignment setting $WIDE_CHAR_BEHAVIOR . Note: Setting the assignment setting or property to use the character set, switches the W packing code to a C packing code, in which case you must also set the $DEF_CHARSET assignment setting or Character Set entity interface property. Related Links Packing Codes for Unicode By default, the W packing code is for Unicode characters. The U* packing code can also be used for holding Unicode characters. If the entity character set is Unicode, the C packing code can also be used for Unicode characters. Character Packing Code (C) The C packing code is used for String data types. Packing Codes for Other Data String, Image, and Raw data can be mapped to a variety of packing codes, including W for Unicode characters. Wide Character Behavior Specify the character set used for String fields with the W packing code. If the database does not support Unicode, or it supports only Unicode BMP, use this setting to change its behavior. Valid values are Unicode, BMP, or Use Character Set. $WIDE_CHAR_BEHAVIOR Specify the character set used for String fields with the W packing code. $DEF_CHARSET Specify the default character set used for storing data in String fields with C packing code. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}